<ol>
<li class="has-line-data" data-line-start="17" data-line-end="18">Update System first</li>
</ol>
<pre><code class="html">dnf -y update
</code></pre>
<ol start="2">
<li class="has-line-data" data-line-start="22" data-line-end="24">Install Helper APP</li>
</ol>
<pre><code class="html">dnf -y install nano curl wget bind-utils 
</code></pre>
<ol start="3">
<li class="has-line-data" data-line-start="29" data-line-end="31">Install LAMP with MariaDB</li>
</ol>
<pre><code class="html">dnf -y install mariadb-server mariadb php php-fpm php-xml php-json php-mysqlnd php-mbstring php-opcache php-gd php-cli firewalld mod_ssl
</code></pre>
<ol start="4">
<li class="has-line-data" data-line-start="36" data-line-end="38">Enable Load on Startup for <code>httpd</code>  <code>MariaDB</code> and <code>PHP-FPM</code></li>
</ol>
<pre><code class="html">systemctl enable httpd.service
systemctl enable php-fpm.service
systemctl enable mariadb.service
</code></pre>
<ol start="5">
<li class="has-line-data" data-line-start="45" data-line-end="46">Configure Firewalld and Allow HTTP/HTTPS</li>
</ol>
<pre><code class="html">firewall-cmd --permanent --zone=public --add-service=http
firewall-cmd --permanent --zone=public --add-service=https
firewall-cmd --reload
</code></pre>
<ol start="6">
<li class="has-line-data" data-line-start="52" data-line-end="53">Create simple PHP Info page to verify PHP is working in Apache in the <code>/var/www/html/info.php</code></li>
</ol>
<pre><code class="html">&lt;?php

phpinfo();
</code></pre>
<ol start="7">
<li class="has-line-data" data-line-start="59" data-line-end="61">Fix the File permissions to purely configured as Non-Root User</li>
</ol>
<pre><code class="html">chown -R apache:apache /etc/run/
chown -R apache:apache /var/www
chown -R apache:apache /etc/httpd 
</code></pre>
<ol start="8">
<li class="has-line-data" data-line-start="67" data-line-end="69">Start the Apache httpd server</li>
</ol>
<pre><code class="html">systemctl start httpd.service
systemctl status httpd
</code></pre>
<ol start="9">
<li class="has-line-data" data-line-start="74" data-line-end="76">Test It</li>
</ol>
<pre><code class="html"># curl -I  http://localhost/        
